President Barack Obama has issued a proclamation declaring March 2, 2015, as Read Across America Day. The proclamation emphasizes the importance of literacy and reading in a child's development and calls on everyone, including children, families, educators, librarians, and public officials, to observe the day with appropriate programs and activities. The proclamation also highlights the works of Dr. Seuss, who has inspired generations of children to love reading. The President encourages everyone to play a part in developing the next generation of readers and writers by supporting resources in classrooms and libraries and engaging young people in reading.